852
01:06:35,909 --> 01:06:40,080
Tell me about your next shipment:
Where it's coming in, how many...

853
01:06:40,247 --> 01:06:42,958
I can't tell you that, Roger.
I can't.

854
01:06:43,625 --> 01:06:48,255
I have another daughter. You can't
protect her. I'm in this too deep.

855
01:07:07,566 --> 01:07:11,153
Heroin.
You got off easy, you son of a bitch!

856
01:07:31,840 --> 01:07:33,008
You through?

857
01:07:33,383 --> 01:07:35,177
I haven't even started.

858
01:07:35,677 --> 01:07:40,015
<i>Gen. McAllister, this is
Delta One. We're coming in. Over.</i>

859
01:07:40,724 --> 01:07:42,824
- Your mission is accomplished?
<i>- Yes, sir.</i>

860
01:07:43,393 --> 01:07:45,604
<i>Mr. Hunsaker is dead, sir.</i>

861
01:07:45,854 --> 01:07:48,732
<i>I'm afraid, however,
that another problem exists.</i>

862
01:07:48,982 --> 01:07:50,609
<i>What is it? Explain.</i>

863
01:07:50,817 --> 01:07:52,819
<i>Hunsaker spoke to the police.</i>

864
01:07:53,153 --> 01:07:56,406
<i>- Are they dead?
- No, I missed the opportunity.</i>

865
01:07:56,657 --> 01:08:00,535
<i>Very disappointing. So the
police may know the whole operation?</i>

866
01:08:00,744 --> 01:08:02,412
<i>That is correct, sir.</i>

867
01:08:03,038 --> 01:08:05,415
Joshua, it's time we turned up the heat.

868
01:08:05,666 --> 01:08:07,125
Come on home.

869
01:08:23,767 --> 01:08:25,185
- Hi.
- Hi.

870
01:08:25,394 --> 01:08:28,355
What's a nice Irish girl
like you doing out here?

871
01:08:28,522 --> 01:08:31,650
I'm looking for a guy,
had this girl in his stable.

872
01:08:31,858 --> 01:08:34,903
- Never seen her.
- She's in your line of work. You sure?

873
01:08:35,195 --> 01:08:37,698
- Sure. Why?
- I'm a police officer.

874
01:08:37,906 --> 01:08:40,575
Don't worry, I won't drag your
ass to jail...

875
01:09:08,103 --> 01:09:09,479
You wore your vest.

876
01:09:10,564 --> 01:09:12,899
That was smart, kid. Come on.

877
01:09:15,110 --> 01:09:17,446
Hold on! I'm on your side.

878
01:09:20,115 --> 01:09:22,576
Son of a bitch, that hurts!

879
01:09:23,243 --> 01:09:25,704
I'm pissed, Roger! Now I'm pissed.

880
01:09:27,497 --> 01:09:28,915
Look at your face!

881
01:09:29,249 --> 01:09:31,418
Two inches higher,
he'd have hit your head.

882
01:09:31,585 --> 01:09:34,212
Two inches lower,
I'd be a falsetto for life.

883
01:09:34,421 --> 01:09:36,298
I bet you'd sound nice too.

884
01:09:38,091 --> 01:09:40,093
- Where's my gun?
- Here.

885
01:09:43,138 --> 01:09:44,848
Oh, shit! Roger!

886
01:09:45,724 --> 01:09:47,768
The guy who shot me...

887
01:09:48,435 --> 01:09:51,938
The same albino jackrabbit
son of a bitch that did Hunsaker.

888
01:09:52,105 --> 01:09:53,774
- You sure?
- I'm sure, man.

889
01:09:53,940 --> 01:09:55,942
I never forget an asshole.

890
01:09:56,234 --> 01:09:57,861
I got an idea.

891
01:09:58,612 --> 01:10:02,282
We fly first class to Detroit
and lay low for a couple weeks.

892
01:10:02,449 --> 01:10:04,826
Come on, be serious.
What do we do?

893
01:10:05,035 --> 01:10:06,161
What else?

894
01:10:06,453 --> 01:10:09,122
We bury the fuckers.
And you know what else?

895
01:10:09,289 --> 01:10:13,460
We do this right, we get famous.
Do shaving ads. Girls. Money.

896
01:10:14,252 --> 01:10:16,880
With our luck, we'll do
Forest Lawn commercials.

897
01:10:17,130 --> 01:10:19,383
Bullshit! We got the edge.

898
01:10:20,467 --> 01:10:24,137
Roger, they think I'm dead.
I'm a corpse.

899
01:10:30,352 --> 01:10:31,812
Brilliant.

900
01:10:33,814 --> 01:10:35,565
Brilliant shit!

901
01:10:38,026 --> 01:10:40,278
- 3-William-56.
<i>- We got a body for you.</i>

902
01:10:40,487 --> 01:10:44,032
He was at Hunsaker's place.
I saw him, he saw me.

903
01:10:44,282 --> 01:10:46,284
Get someone else to do it, okay?

904
01:10:46,576 --> 01:10:50,705
<i>Captain says give it to you.
About two blocks from your house.</i>

905
01:10:51,206 --> 01:10:54,918
Yeah, sure. He's probably blond
with big dimples.

906
01:10:55,293 --> 01:10:57,587
<i>How did you know that, sarge?</i>

907
01:10:59,548 --> 01:11:01,591
- Get in here!
- What's the matter?

908
01:11:01,883 --> 01:11:02,926
Trouble.

909
01:11:06,304 --> 01:11:10,183
They just gave a description
of the kid my daughter's dating.

910
01:11:37,627 --> 01:11:39,838
Let's be dark and quiet.

911
01:12:03,945 --> 01:12:06,072
One, two...

912
01:12:21,129 --> 01:12:23,381
The bastards got my daughter.

913
01:12:34,768 --> 01:12:35,769
What is it?

914
01:12:36,394 --> 01:12:37,395
Nothing.

915
01:12:37,604 --> 01:12:39,105
- What is it?
- Nothing!

916
01:12:39,397 --> 01:12:42,108
Get back in your room.
Back in your room!

917
01:12:58,166 --> 01:12:59,167
Murtaugh.

918
01:12:59,459 --> 01:13:01,419
<i>You have a beautiful daughter.</i>

919
01:13:01,628 --> 01:13:05,048
<i>I'd stick by the phone to find out
where to meet us.</i>

920
01:13:11,054 --> 01:13:12,806
They got my kid.

921
01:13:14,558 --> 01:13:16,643
Bastards took my baby.

922
01:13:40,166 --> 01:13:42,752
<i>Sgt. McCaskey, pick up line three.</i>

923
01:13:43,587 --> 01:13:45,338
Homicide, McCaskey speaking.

924
01:13:45,547 --> 01:13:46,881
This is KCOP news.

925
01:13:47,090 --> 01:13:51,511
We heard an officer was shot tonight.
Can you give us more information?

926
01:13:51,720 --> 01:13:55,515
Sgt. Martin Riggs was shot and killed.
Who is this?

927
01:13:55,682 --> 01:13:57,684
We'll send somebody right over.

928
01:14:02,188 --> 01:14:04,691
Bingo! Riggs is out of the picture.

929
01:14:05,108 --> 01:14:06,860
I want Murtaugh taken alive.

930
01:14:07,402 --> 01:14:08,862
He may not talk.

931
01:14:10,113 --> 01:14:12,032
We have his little girl.
He'll talk.

932
01:14:28,131 --> 01:14:31,009
You know they're gonna kill her,
don't you?

933
01:14:31,635 --> 01:14:32,636
Yes.

934
01:14:34,262 --> 01:14:38,725
And if you want her back,
you'll have to take her away from them.

935
01:14:39,059 --> 01:14:40,310
I know.

936
01:14:45,732 --> 01:14:49,653
We do this my way.
You shoot and you shoot to kill.

937
01:14:50,153 --> 01:14:54,616
Get as many as you can.
All you got to do is just not miss.

938
01:14:54,824 --> 01:14:56,409
I won't miss.

939
01:14:58,411 --> 01:15:01,289
We're going to get bloody on this one.

940
01:15:05,460 --> 01:15:07,170
Are you really crazy?

941
01:15:09,923 --> 01:15:12,258
Or are you as good as you say you are?

942
01:15:14,344 --> 01:15:16,262
You're gonna have to trust me.

943
01:15:20,266 --> 01:15:21,601
Here we go.

944
01:15:26,940 --> 01:15:28,066
Murtaugh.

945
01:15:28,274 --> 01:15:32,570
<i>We don't want your daughter.
We want to know what Hunsaker told you.</i>

946
01:15:32,779 --> 01:15:36,783
<i>Dry lake. Victorville.
Sunrise tomorrow. Be there.</i>

947
01:18:42,010 --> 01:18:43,344
Murtaugh!

948
01:18:43,970 --> 01:18:45,388
Yes, that's right.

949
01:18:45,638 --> 01:18:47,640
Show me my daughter!

950
01:18:47,932 --> 01:18:50,768
Let me see her, then I'll come quietly.

951
01:18:57,734 --> 01:18:59,402
He wants to see the girl.

952
01:18:59,652 --> 01:19:00,862
Get out.

953
01:19:06,492 --> 01:19:07,785
Daddy!

954
01:19:08,286 --> 01:19:10,580
Okay, baby! I'm here.

955
01:19:11,080 --> 01:19:12,999
Okay, it's all right.

956
01:19:13,207 --> 01:19:14,208
Simple exchange.

957
01:19:15,293 --> 01:19:18,838
You come with us, the girl takes a walk.

958
01:19:19,088 --> 01:19:20,548
Let her go now.

959
01:19:22,842 --> 01:19:26,387
As I say, take your hands
out of your pockets.

960
01:19:26,596 --> 01:19:28,306
Sure thing, pal.

961
01:19:32,101 --> 01:19:33,102
It's alive.

962
01:19:35,605 --> 01:19:38,232
Let her go now, or we all die.

963
01:19:39,067 --> 01:19:40,193
Take him!

964
01:19:40,526 --> 01:19:41,736
He has a grenade!

965
01:19:42,028 --> 01:19:44,948
He's bluffing!
He wouldn't risk killing his daughter.

966
01:19:45,740 --> 01:19:47,325
If she's gonna die...

967
01:19:47,533 --> 01:19:50,954
...she's gonna die with me.
My way, not yours.

968
01:19:56,125 --> 01:20:00,546
Come on, Roger, get out of the way.
Move to your left. Come on!

969
01:20:00,755 --> 01:20:02,215
Put the pin back in.

970
01:20:02,715 --> 01:20:06,552
Officer Murtaugh, don't be foolish.
Look at the hardware.

971
01:20:06,886 --> 01:20:08,554
Move to your left.

972
01:20:14,227 --> 01:20:17,730
Look at the firepower.
You're grounded. Riggs is gone.

973
01:20:18,064 --> 01:20:20,233
Put the pin back in the grenade.

974
01:20:20,441 --> 01:20:22,068
